The Lady Vol rowing team competed successfully in the Head of the Ohio on Oct PERIOD  despite the fact that the event was cut short due to high prevailing winds PERIOD The regatta was halfway into completion when officials canceled the rest of the event due to steady winds from the west that were creating gusts as high  mph PERIOD

The Lady Vols competed in three of the four races they were entered in along the .8mile course before the weather forced the end of the event PERIOD In the Club  race the Orange and White team of Shannon McMahon Lauren Kueck Grace Harrington Joyce Kranzke and Kristen Logan were victorious with a time of . pERIOD Behind them was a team from Michigan State that clocked in at . pERIOD Another Lady Vol team took third with a time of . pERIOD The crew for that shell was Erika Twedt Kelly Kraiss Kay Logan Ashley Smith and Marie Hanscom PERIOD In fourth place was the other Big Orange team of Lizzie Brown Kacey Montgomery Ginny Bradley Tammy Horton and Erin Moore who recorded a time of . pERIOD The team also raced in the Youth  and Open  but results are currently unavailable PERIOD The Club  race was the only casualty on the day PERIOD

Head Coach Lisa Glenn will now prepare her team for the Head of Lake Hartwell and Head of the Tennessee events in late October PERIOD
